<div id="review_4439467664" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4439467664" />
    <a title="Emily" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23343364-emily"><img alt="Emily" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1513816621p2/23343364.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4439467664?book_show_action=true">Jan 06, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily" href="/user/show/23343364-emily">Emily</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23343364-emily?shelf=biography">biography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4439467664" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2202582990551568191">A biography of Dietrich Bonhoeffer by Eric Metaxes. <br/><br/>I knew very little about Bonhoeffer before reading this book, and I found out that some of what I knew was wrong, since I had confused him with someone else. Now, however, I know more than I imagined I would when I started the biography. <br/><br/>The book was very informative. Metaxes wrote about many details not only of Bonhoeffer&apos;s life but also of his doctrine and speeches, of others in his life, and of the political and social contexts of the time. </span>
  <span id="freeText2202582990551568191" style="display:none">A biography of Dietrich Bonhoeffer by Eric Metaxes. <br /><br />I knew very little about Bonhoeffer before reading this book, and I found out that some of what I knew was wrong, since I had confused him with someone else. Now, however, I know more than I imagined I would when I started the biography. <br /><br />The book was very informative. Metaxes wrote about many details not only of Bonhoeffer's life but also of his doctrine and speeches, of others in his life, and of the political and social contexts of the time. He included quotes from Bonhoeffer, his friends, and his family throughout the novel, and he wrote about Bonhoeffer's theology to some extent as well. <br /><br />One thing I didn't always appreciate was the many times the author mentioned something that was going to happen in the future. Most of the book is told chronologically, and I didn't appreciate when the author wrote in unnecessary "spoilers." It was a biography and some events of Bonhoeffer's life are fairly well-known, but I still didn't like the spoilers. <br /><br />I read this book as an audiobook, sped up as is my usual practice. Still, it was very long. The audiobook narrator was great. <br /><br />I enjoyed this book, learned much from it, and would highly recommend it to serious readers. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2202582990551568191" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


